This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it deals with generative adversarial networks (GANs) and their learning objectives. Additionally, the paper focuses on image generation benchmarks, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel practical objective, which indicates that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of Lagrangian relaxation and optimization techniques suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with image generation.
